bug.short_desc: Newsletter form layout broken on What's New page

long_desc.thetext:
Created attachment 523988 Screenshot of broken layout on newsletter form on whatsnew page
The email newsletter sign-up form layout is broken on the whatsnew page. Screenshot attached.

Created attachment 524224 jlongster's view
Steven, I can't reproduce that. When I added the Spark promo that happened but I fixed it.
Attached what I see.

James, I think this is a matter of a fixed width (on the "#newsletter-signup .title" div) that contains a headline. The exact size of the font varies per platform due to system font-rendering details. This is causing the "Keep In Touch" headline to wrap on some systems.
Making that element a bit wider would help. I'm also not sure why it has a fixed height (40px) - if the height was left as auto, even if the text did wrap, there would be no overlapping.
That doesn't address the Twitter/Spark buttons wrapping - I suspect that is also a font-size issue on both the buttons themselves, and the Country flydown.
